LEWIS v. FLORIDA. No. 80,

Misc.

Decided October 14, 1957. H. M. Rosenhouse for appellant. Richard W. Ervin, Attorney General of Florida, and David U. Tumin, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The appeal is dismissed. Treating the papers whereon the appeal was taken as a petition for writ of certiorari, certiorari is denied.
